Air Supply, Air and Abrasive Media Purity
Reference Standard: Blotter Test - ASTM D-4285 (Perform Daily)
Reference Standard: Abrasive Blasting - AS 1627 Part: Part 4 Abrasive Blast Cleaning (Written)
Reference Standard: AS 1627 Part 9: Pictorial Standard
Client Specification: Class 2½ Near White Metal”

"Class 2.5" Very thorough blast cleaning. When viewed without magnification, the surface shall be free from visible oil, grease and dirt, and shall be free from mill scale, rust, paint coatings and foreign matter. Any remaining contamination shall show only as slight stains in the form of spots or stripes and correspond to the prints designated Sa 2½ in AS 1627.9.
Reference Standard: ASTM D 4417-21 Method B or AS 3984.5 Method D
Reference Standard: AS 3894 - 7 Method / SSPC PA 1
Follow the parameters of Technical Data Sheet/ Specification (See Information below)

All painting is to be performed under cover and/or protected from rain, condensation, dew, excessive wind, overspray or wind-blown dust, or where any of these conditions will exist or develop before the coating has cured to a satisfactory degree so as to be unaffected. The foregoing specifically relates to conditions during the night-time after coating application.
Final surface preparation or coating application shall NOT take place when:
(a) The relative humidity is above 85 percent; or
(b) The substrate temperature is less than 3°C above the dewpoint; or
(c) The ambient air temperature is below 5°C or above 40°C; or
(d) The substrate temperature is below 10°C or above 35°C; or
(e) The surface to be coated is wet or damp; or
(e) Where the full prime coat application cannot be carried out before the specified cleanliness of the surface deteriorates.
Generally, coatings shall not to be applied to substrate temperatures below 10°C without reference to DULUX.

In the case where a preliminary blast or other surface preparation is being carried out, it may be performed in conditions that are outside the above limits providing the final surface preparation and all coating application is undertaken in accordance with the above.
Dry Film Coating Thickness Readings and Wet Film Requirements
Materials shall be applied so as to produce an even coating free from film defects; e.g. missed areas, voids, overspray, overbuild, lumps, runs, sags and/or inclusions.
